comments:
That part of the unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the urban district 
    of Skelton & Brotton and the parishes of Brotton, Kilton, Mooresholm, Skelton and Stanghow. Abolished 1.4.1982 and divided between the parishes of Skelton 
    & Brotton, Lockwood and Loftus. See also Table 2, note (a).
Created 1.4.1982 out of the Langbaurgh unparished area.See also Table 2, note (b).

Created 1.4.1974 from the parishes of Saltburn by the Sea and 
    Marske. Renamed 1.4.1983 to become the parish of Saltburn, Marske & New Marske. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).

Created 1.4.1983 by renaming the parish of Saltburn & Marske by 
    the Sea. See also Table 2, note (b).
Created 1.4.1982 out of the Langbaurgh unparished area. See also Table 2, note (b).
